Note: git rebase --continue
                           when we are rebasing and see conflict,
                           after resolving the conflict
                           we need to continue (use this command)
                           but intellij do it for us (after resolving conflicts)
      git rebase --skip
                           when we are rebasing and see conflict,
                           some times we figure out the first commit (the current commit that git want to rebase)
                           is not really necessary!
                           we just skip it (it means we remove it permanently!)
                           some times it can remove conflict!
                           main:    A---B---C
                                          \           -->  main:   A---B---C---E'---F'
                           feature:        D---E---F               (D is removed by skipping!)

      git rebase --abort
                           because we are entered to some combination mood by rebasing
                           we have conflict flag, some new files that prepare combination,....
                           we need aborting, if we want back to point before rebasing!